==Albanian==
===Etymology===
A Slavic loanword, akin to Romanian ''[[raţă]]''
    Old Church Slavic rosa `dew', lit. rasà ds. 
Maybe as `*water bird' in alb. rosa f. `female duck (*water bird)' : Slovenian: raca f. `female duck' : Romany: ratsoy m. `male duck', ratsa f. `female duck' : Romanian: raţă f. `female duck', răţoi m. `male duck'.
For more information see http://www.geocities.com/protoillyrian/

